<description>Thomas became the successor to the legendary Peter Schmeichel in the Denmark goal and, after keeping a club record 30 clean sheets for Sunderland during the 1998-99 season, was also linked to taking over his gloves at Manchester United.
A commanding figure in the penalty area with excellent handling skills, he joined Sunderland from Odense BK in August 1998 for ï¿½500,000 and became a stalwart of their Premiership line-up.
Thomas made his full international debut in the Euro 2000 Play-Off against Israel.
Thomas joined Aston Villa in August 2003 on a three-year contract that was extended to June 2008 in August 2005.
He joined Stoke City in July 2008 with a three-year contract.</description>

